title: Westbrook's 38, triple-double lead Thunder past Grizzlies
text:
Westbrook's 38, triple-double lead Thunder past Grizzlies Russell Westbrook scored 19 of his 38 points in the fourth quarter and had a triple-double to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder past the Memphis Grizzlies 114-102 Post to Facebook Westbrook's 38, triple-double lead Thunder past Grizzlies Russell Westbrook scored 19 of his 38 points in the fourth quarter and had a triple-double to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder past the Memphis Grizzlies 114-102  //usat.ly/2l2GzJP   Westbrook's 38, triple-double lead Thunder past Grizzlies AP 10:57 p.m. ET Feb. 3, 2017 Memphis Grizzlies center Marc Gasol, right, shoots over Oklahoma City Thunder forward Andre Roberson (21) during the first quarter of an NBA basketball game in Oklahoma City, Friday, Feb. 3, 2017. (AP Photo/Sue Ogrocki) (Photo: The Associated Press) 
OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) â€” Russell Westbrook scored 19 of his 38 points in the fourth quarter and had a triple-double to lead the Oklahoma City Thunder past the Memphis Grizzlies 114-102 on Friday night. 
Westbrook also had 13 rebounds and 12 assists. It was his 25th triple-double this season and the 62nd of his career. His season total is the most in the NBA since Wilt Chamberlain had 31 during the 1967-68 season. 
Steven Adams had 16 points and 13 rebounds, Joffrey Lauvergne scored a season-high 16 points and Anthony Morrow added 15 points for the Thunder, who snapped a three-game losing streak. 
Marc Gasol scored 31 points, Mike Conley had 18 and Zach Randolph added 16 for the Grizzlies, who shot 48 percent overall but just 3 of 19 on 3-pointers.
